---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Lisa Wilkins | UX Design & Strategy"
  description="Lisa Wilkins is a UX Director, Product Strategist, and Agentic Builder with 17+ years building products for scale at NBCUniversal, PragerU, and Microsoft."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-white pt-20 pb-16 px-6" aria-labelledby="hero-heading">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h1 id="hero-heading" class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-extrabold text-[var(--color-charcoal)] leading-none tracking-tight mb-6">
        Lisa Wilkins
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-mid-gray)] uppercase tracking-widest">
        Agentic Builder&nbsp;&nbsp;·&nbsp;&nbsp;UX Director&nbsp;&nbsp;·&nbsp;&nbsp;Product Strategist
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Case study 1: NBC News -->
  <section class="bg-white py-16 px-6 border-t border-[var(--color-border)]" aria-labelledby="nbc-heading">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">
      <div>
        <h2 id="nbc-heading" class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6 leading-tight">
          Building for scale &amp; flexibility
        </h2>
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-[var(--color-dark-gray)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Solutions for NOW are valuable. Solutions for LATER pay you back. At NBCUniversal, I architected component systems and content frameworks across NBC News, TODAY, and Telemundo that supported 1.5M+ daily users, and kept scaling through two full app redesigns with a flexible foundation. That meant understanding the tech stack deeply enough to design for future growth.
        </p>
        <a
          href="/nbc-news"
          class="inline-block mt-4 bg-[var(--color-coral)] hover:bg-[var(--color-coral-hover)] text-white text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest px-6 py-3 rounded-md transition-colors"
        >
          View NBC App Redesign
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Case study 2: Strategy -->
  <section class="bg-[var(--color-light-bg)] py-16 px-6" aria-labelledby="strategy-heading">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">
      <div>
        <h2 id="strategy-heading" class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6 leading-tight">
          From complexity to clarity
        </h2>
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-[var(--color-dark-gray)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
          I've made a career of stepping back, finding the signal, and building the simple, scalable structure underneath. Whether inherited or fresh earth, I bring the same approach: distill the chaos into foundational components, align the competing requirements, and deliver a system that serves the product long after the launch.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-[var(--color-dark-gray)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
          I've built and inherited a platform serving 1.3M+ monthly users across web, mobile, and OTT with no unified content architecture. I distilled convoluted user journeys, organized content taxonomies, and broke down competing business requirements into foundational components — work that streamlined delivery cycles by 43% and extended well beyond any single release. The hardest, yet most rewarding, part of design is making things simple.
        </p>
        <a
          href="/strategy"
          class="inline-block mt-4 bg-[var(--color-slate)] hover:bg-[var(--color-slate-hover)] text-white text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest px-6 py-3 rounded-md transition-colors"
        >
          View Product Strategy Impact
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Human Centered interstitial -->
  <section class="bg-[var(--color-charcoal)] py-12 px-6" aria-label="Human centered">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-extrabold text-white leading-none tracking-tight opacity-15 select-none" aria-hidden="true">
        HUMAN<br />CENTERED
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Test, learn, pivot -->
  <section class="bg-white py-16 px-6" aria-labelledby="test-learn-heading">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto max-w-2xl">
      <h2 id="test-learn-heading" class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6 leading-tight">
        Test, learn, pivot
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-[var(--color-dark-gray)] leading-relaxed">
        At NBCUniversal and PragerU, I fostered team environments where critical thinking and candid feedback became expected. That foundation made usability testing, market analysis, and data-driven iteration more than process checkboxes; at PragerU, it's how I demonstrated the value of qualitative user testing to an executive team that was initially skeptical.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Unity section -->
  <section class="bg-[var(--color-cream)] py-16 px-6" aria-labelledby="unity-heading">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto max-w-2xl">
      <h2 id="unity-heading" class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6 leading-tight">
        Unity nourishes your competitive advantage
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-[var(--color-dark-gray)] leading-relaxed">
        Early in my career, Sara Fortier's work on North Star Principals reshaped how I think about product leadership. Building a shared vision provides cross-functional partners a single point of alignment. When everyone is building toward the same outcome, collaboration stops being a process problem and becomes a competitive advantage.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Leading by example -->
  <section class="bg-white py-16 px-6" aria-labelledby="leading-heading">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 id="leading-heading" class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-12 leading-tight">
        Leading by example
      </h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-10">
        <article>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-extrabold text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3 uppercase tracking-wide">Allied Collaborator</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-dark-gray)] leading-relaxed">
            I build trust through candid, proactive communication. Surfacing problems early keeps teams and their stakeholders informed and aligned.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-extrabold text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3 uppercase tracking-wide">Workflow Architect</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-dark-gray)] leading-relaxed">
            I close skills gaps and redesign front- and backstage processes so teams can move fluidly. At PragerU, this reduced product delivery cycle time by 43%.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-extrabold text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3 uppercase tracking-wide">WCAG Advocate</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-dark-gray)] leading-relaxed">
            Accessibility isn't a final checklist. I embed WCAG compliance from project kickoff. I led initiatives that improved accessibility scores from 55% to 85% across multiple platforms.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Hello / Bio -->
  <section class="bg-[var(--color-light-bg)] py-16 px-6" aria-labelledby="hello-heading">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto max-w-2xl">
      <h2 id="hello-heading" class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6 leading-tight">
        Hello!
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-[var(--color-dark-gray)] leading-relaxed mb-8">
        I'm Lisa Wilkins. I've spent 17+ years as a UX director, designer, and product strategist building things people actually want to use — across media, news, tech, and education at organizations like NBCUniversal, PragerU, and Microsoft. I live in the Sonoran Desert, which inspires me daily with its simplicity on the surface and complexity underneath. I'm adaptable, resilient, and nerdy — ask me about WCAG compliance or horse training and you'll get the same enthusiasm. I'm most proud of raising a son full of gratitude and spoiling a very good dog.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base md:text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--color-dark-gray)] mb-8">
        Let's talk about what I can build with your team.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/connect"
        class="inline-block bg-[var(--color-coral)] hover:bg-[var(--color-coral-hover)] text-white text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest px-8 py-4 rounded-md transition-colors"
      >
        Connect
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
